In Hindu and Sikh traditions, the term '''Agya''' refers to commandment or order <ref>The Oxford Hindi/English dictionary published by Oxford University Press 1995, edited by R.S. McGregor.</ref> of a spiritual Master to a disciple<ref>[http://www.mudrashram.com/glossarypage.html Mudrashram Institute of Spiritual Studies - Glossary]</ref>.

== Other uses==
*Agya [[chakra]] or [[third eye]] chackra at the eye-brow junction. 


